    "markdown": "---\ntitle: La Mejor Masa de Pizza para Marcelo\nsubtitle: Uso de Quarto + Typst para reportes científicos\nheader: Por favor haga click [AQUÍ](https://github.com/equihuam/prueba-git) para ir al documento en Github.\nauthor:\n  - name: Miguel Equihua\n    email: miguel.equihua@inecol.mx\n    orcid: 0000-0001-5306-7397\n    affiliations:\n      - name: Inecol\n      \nabstract: |\n  {{< lipsum 1 >}}\nthanks: |\n  This template is inspired by Kieran Healy's [LaTeX and Rmd template](https://github.com/kjhealy/latex-custom-kjh) and\n  Andrew Heiss's [Hikmah Quarto template](https://github.com/andrewheiss/hikmah-academic-quarto).\nkeywords: [Quarto, Typst, format]\nlang: es\ncustom-keywords:\n  - name: JEL Codes\n    values: [J16, J22, J31]    \ndate: today\ndate-format: full\nbibliography: paper-refs.bib\n\nparams:\n  es_html: true\n\nformat:\n    html: default\n    docx: default\n    academic-typst:\n      section-numbering: \"1.1.1\"\n      font-paths: [\"./static/fonts\"]\n      mainfont: \"Libertinus serif\"\n      sansfont: Jost\n      mathfont: \"Libertinus Math\"\n      bibliographystyle: \"american-psychological-association\"  \n      include-in-header:\n        - text: '#import \"@preview/mitex:0.2.4\": *'      \nexecute: \n  echo: false \n  warning: false\n---\n\nThis document shows a practical usage of the template.\n\nI use the Palmer penguins dataset [@horst2020] to demonstrate the features of the template.\nThe code is available [here](https://github.com/kazuyanagimoto/quarto-academic-typst).\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n# Section as Heading Level 1\n\nSection numbering can be specified in the YAML `section-numbering` field\nas other Typst templates.\n\n## Subsection as Heading Level 2\n\nYou can use LaTeX math expressions:\n\n$$\nY_{it} = \\alpha_i + \\lambda_t + \\sum_{k \\neq -1} \\tau_h \\mathbb{1}\\{E_i + k = t\\} +\n\\varepsilon_{it}.\n$$\n\nI choose a mathematical font which supports the indicator function $\\mathbb{1}\\{\\cdot\\}$.\nCurrently, I use the {{< meta mathfont >}} font.\n\n### Subsubsection as Heading Level 3\n\nI don't use and don't recommend using heading levels 3 and below but it works.\n\n## Citation\n\nYou can cite a reference like this [@katsushika1831] or @horst2020.\nTypst has some built-in citation styles. Check the [Typst documentation](https://typst.app/docs/reference/model/bibliography/#parameters-style) for more information.\n\n# Figures and Tables\n\n## Figures\n\nAs @fig-facet shows, the caption is displayed below the figure.\nAs a caption of the figure (`fig-cap`), I use bold text for the title and use a normal text for the description.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![**Flipper Length and Bill Length of Penguins**.\nThe x-axis shows the flipper length, and the y-axis shows the bill length.](articulo-pizza_files/figure-html/fig-facet-1.png){#fig-facet width=576}\n:::\n:::\n\n\nWhen I want to show multiple figures side by side, I use the `patchwork` package.\nThe reason why I don't use the `layout-col` option is that the caption is also split into two parts.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![**Characteristics of Penguins**.\nThe left panel shows the relationship between flipper length and body mass.\nThe right panel shows the density of flipper length.](articulo-pizza_files/figure-html/fig-patchwork-1.png){#fig-patchwork width=576}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n## Tables\n\nYou can use [tinytable](https://vincentarelbundock.github.io/tinytable/)\nfor general tables and [modelsummary](https://vincentarelbundock.github.io/modelsummary/) for regression tables.\nAs @tbl-sum-penguins shows, the caption is displayed above the table.\nThe notes of the table can be added using the `notes` argument of the `tinytable::tt()` function.\n\n\n::: {#tbl-sum-penguins .cell tbl-cap='Summary Statistics of Penguins'}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<!-- preamble start -->\n\n    <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/vincentarelbundock/tinytable@main/inst/tinytable.js\"></script>\n\n    <script>\n      // Create table-specific functions using external factory\n      const tableFns_hx9rovjc7sjeknjvq8xg = TinyTable.createTableFunctions(\"tinytable_hx9rovjc7sjeknjvq8xg\");\n      // tinytable span after\n      window.addEventListener('load', function () {\n          var cellsToStyle = [\n            // tinytable style arrays after\n          { positions: [ { i: '-1', j: 5 } ], css_id: 'tinytable_css_q5cm81nkl93jk1kghjiq',}, \n          { positions: [ { i: '-1', j: 3 }, { i: '-1', j: 4 }, { i: '-1', j: 7 }, { i: '-1', j: 8 }, { i: '-1', j: 9 } ], css_id: 'tinytable_css_kfyallq65y7th818kul0',}, \n          { positions: [ { i: '-1', j: 2 }, { i: '-1', j: 6 } ], css_id: 'tinytable_css_35dqgpqyl1nc1mmyr6er',}, \n          { positions: [ { i: '3', j: 1 }, { i: '3', j: 2 }, { i: '3', j: 3 }, { i: '3', j: 4 }, { i: '3', j: 5 }, { i: '3', j: 6 }, { i: '3', j: 7 }, { i: '3', j: 8 }, { i: '3', j: 9 } ], css_id: 'tinytable_css_oyf2sufhqp6wcg0vooo5',}, \n          { positions: [ { i: '0', j: 1 }, { i: '0', j: 2 }, { i: '0', j: 3 }, { i: '0', j: 4 }, { i: '0', j: 5 }, { i: '0', j: 6 }, { i: '0', j: 7 }, { i: '0', j: 8 }, { i: '0', j: 9 } ], css_id: 'tinytable_css_inr1xa2j1ylu8cd4tq30',}, \n          { positions: [ { i: '-1', j: 1 } ], css_id: 'tinytable_css_wc98fpic849mzutiwvsa',}, \n          ];\n\n          // Loop over the arrays to style the cells\n          cellsToStyle.forEach(function (group) {\n              group.positions.forEach(function (cell) {\n                  tableFns_hx9rovjc7sjeknjvq8xg.styleCell(cell.i, cell.j, group.css_id);\n              });\n          });\n      });\n    </script>\n\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/vincentarelbundock/tinytable@main/inst/tinytable.css\">\n    <style>\n    /* tinytable css entries after */\n    #tinytable_hx9rovjc7sjeknjvq8xg td.tinytable_css_q5cm81nkl93jk1kghjiq, #tinytable_hx9rovjc7sjeknjvq8xg th.tinytable_css_q5cm81nkl